.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::MediaAttachment \- NIP\-92 Media Attachments
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::MediaAttachment;
\&
\&    # Build an imeta tag
\&    my $tag = Net::Nostr::MediaAttachment\->imeta_tag(
\&        url      => \*(Aqhttps://example.com/photo.jpg\*(Aq,
\&        m        => \*(Aqimage/jpeg\*(Aq,
\&        dim      => \*(Aq1920x1080\*(Aq,
\&        alt      => \*(AqA scenic photo\*(Aq,
\&        blurhash => \*(AqeVF$^OI\*(Aq,
\&        fallback => [\*(Aqhttps://alt.example.com/photo.jpg\*(Aq],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Attach to an event
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Event\->new(
\&        pubkey  => $pubkey,
\&        kind    => 1,
\&        content => \*(AqCheck this out https://example.com/photo.jpg\*(Aq,
\&        tags    => [$tag],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse imeta tags from an event
\&    my @attachments = Net::Nostr::MediaAttachment\->from_event($event);
\&    for my $att (@attachments) {
\&        say $att\->url;
\&        say $att\->m;        # MIME type
\&        say $att\->dim;      # e.g. \*(Aq1920x1080\*(Aq
\&        say $att\->alt;      # accessibility description
\&    }
\&
\&    # Get metadata for a specific URL
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::MediaAttachment\->for_url($event, $url);
.Ve
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 6
\&    my $att = Net::Nostr::MediaAttachment\->new(
\&        url      => \*(Aqhttps://example.com/photo.jpg\*(Aq,
\&        m        => \*(Aqimage/jpeg\*(Aq,
\&        dim      => \*(Aq1920x1080\*(Aq,
\&        fallback => [\*(Aqhttps://alt.example.com/photo.jpg\*(Aq],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new media attachment object. All fields are optional.
\&\f(CW\*(C`fallback\*(C'\fR defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`fields\*(C'\fR defaults to \f(CW\*(C`{}\*(C'\fR.
Croaks on unknown arguments.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-92 (Media Attachments). Provides methods to build \f(CW\*(C`imeta\*(C'\fR
tags, parse them from events, and look up metadata by URL.
.PP
Each \f(CW\*(C`imeta\*(C'\fR tag is variadic with space\-delimited key/value entries. It
MUST have a \f(CW\*(C`url\*(C'\fR and at least one other field. Fields from NIP\-94 are
supported: \f(CW\*(C`m\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`x\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`ox\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`size\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`dim\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`magnet\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`blurhash\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`thumb\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`image\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`summary\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`alt\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`service\*(C'\fR, and
\&\f(CW\*(C`fallback\*(C'\fR (which may appear multiple times).
.SS imeta_tag
.IX Subsection "imeta_tag"
.Vb 8
\&    my $tag = Net::Nostr::MediaAttachment\->imeta_tag(
\&        url      => \*(Aqhttps://example.com/photo.jpg\*(Aq,
\&        m        => \*(Aqimage/jpeg\*(Aq,
\&        dim      => \*(Aq1920x1080\*(Aq,
\&        alt      => \*(AqDescription\*(Aq,
\&        x        => $sha256_hex,
\&        fallback => [\*(Aqhttps://alt1.com/photo.jpg\*(Aq],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates an \f(CW\*(C`imeta\*(C'\fR tag arrayref. \f(CW\*(C`url\*(C'\fR is required, and at least one
other field must be provided. \f(CW\*(C`fallback\*(C'\fR accepts an arrayref of URLs.
.SS from_tag
.IX Subsection "from_tag"
.Vb 3
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::MediaAttachment\->from_tag($imeta_tag);
\&    say $info\->url;
\&    say $info\->m;
.Ve
.PP
Parses a single \f(CW\*(C`imeta\*(C'\fR tag arrayref into a Net::Nostr::MediaAttachment
object. Unknown fields are available via the \f(CW\*(C`fields\*(C'\fR accessor hashref.
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my @attachments = Net::Nostr::MediaAttachment\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Returns a list of Net::Nostr::MediaAttachment objects, one for each
\&\f(CW\*(C`imeta\*(C'\fR tag in the event.
.SS for_url
.IX Subsection "for_url"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::MediaAttachment\->for_url($event, $url);
.Ve
.PP
Returns the Net::Nostr::MediaAttachment for the given URL, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR
if not found.
